        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 3:19PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tuttle Creek Lake, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Hail damage to outdoor objects
and vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuttle Creek Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
